properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 14 at 3:25AM PST until January 14 at 1:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...None.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts 55 to 65 mph
expected across the Eastern Sierra. Wind prone areas such as
Lee Vining, Antelope Valley, and near the Mammoth Airport
could see gusts over 70 mph. Sierra crest ridge gusts over 100
mph.

* WHERE...Mono County.

* WHEN...From 10 PM Monday to 1 PM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees, fences, and
power lines. Power outages are possible. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Severe
turbulence for aviation with delays and cancellations likely.
Increased potential for enhanced fire danger with the strong
winds and relatively dry conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Brief light snow showers remain possible
through this morning with could result in slick spots for the
morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time Secure loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture, holiday decorations, and trash cans before winds
increase which could blow these items away. The best thing to do
is prepare ahead of time by making sure you have extra food and
water on hand, flashlights with spare batteries and/or candles in
the event of a power outage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON
